President Uhuru Kenyatta and COTU Secretary General Francis Atwoli have today joined workers as they celebrate Labour Day at Nyayo National Stadium. This year's gathering is the first in-person meeting since Covid-19 struck Kenya in 2020. This day is set aside to honour and recognize labourers and workers' unions for their contributions to the country. Labour CS Simon Chelugui also attended the celebrations. Other leaders who attended the celebrations are Nairobi Governor Anne Kananu, Nairobi Woman Rep Esther Passaris and ODM secretary-general ODM Edwin Sifuna.